Simulating data

We start with points drawn from Gaussian Distribution.

set.seed(9)
X <- matrix(rnorm(400), 200, 2)
qplot(X[,1], X[,2]) +
  geom_density_2d()

We want the data to have a certai structure that we want it to be able to observe within the processing. We are intersted in correlated data, hence we will multiply the random points drawn from Gaussian Distribution by a special matrix that will transform our data into correlated points.

# A <- matrix(runif(4), 2, 2)
A <- cbind(c(1, 0.5), c(0.5, 1))
Y <- X %*% A
qplot(Y[,1], Y[,2]) +
  geom_density_2d()

Principal Component Analysis

pca_ <- prcomp(Y)
pca_$rotation
            PC1        PC2
[1,] -0.7047889  0.7094170
[2,] -0.7094170 -0.7047889

Explained variance

var_expl <-
  pca_$sdev^2 / sum(pca_$sdev^2)
var_expl
[1] 0.90637322 0.09362678
tmp <- Y %*% pca_$rotation 
plt_pca <-
  qplot(tmp[,1], tmp[,2]) + # equivalent to: qplot(pca_$x[,1], pca_$x[,2])
  labs(x = "PC1", y = "PC2") +
  geom_density2d(alpha = .4) +
  labs(title = "Principal Component projection")
plt_pca

pc_coord <- 
  data.frame(x = pca_$center[1], y = pca_$center[2], 
           xend = pca_$rotation[1,] * sqrt(var_expl) * 3 + pca_$center[1],
           yend = pca_$rotation[2,] * sqrt(var_expl) * 3 + pca_$center[2], 
           component = paste("PC", 1:ncol(pca_$x)))


plt_original_coord <- 
  as_tibble(Y) %>%
  ggplot(aes(V1, V2)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .4) +
  geom_density2d(alpha = .4) +
  geom_segment(data = pc_coord, aes(x, y, xend = xend, yend = yend), size = 1,
               arrow = arrow(type = "closed", length = unit(0.1, "inches"))) +
  coord_equal() +
  labs(title = "Original data with PC coordinates") +
  theme(legend.position = "none") 
`as_tibble.matrix()` requires a matrix with column names or a `.name_repair` argument. Using compatibility `.name_repair`.

PCA as a dimensionality reduction method

pc1 <- tibble(x = c(pca_$center[1], pca_$rotation[1, 1] + pca_$center[1]), 
              y = c(pca_$center[2], pca_$rotation[2, 1] + pca_$center[2]))
pc1_line <- lm(y~x, pc1)
Y_ <- cbind(Y[,1],
            predict(pc1_line, newdata = as_tibble(Y) %>% rename(x=1, y=2)))

as_tibble(rbind(Y, Y_)) %>%
  mutate(source = c(rep("original data", 200),
                    rep("1D projection", 200))) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_point(aes(V1, V2, color = source, shape = source)) +
  #coord_equal() +
  labs(title = "1D projection of the points", shape = "", color = "")  +
  scale_color_uchicago()

PCs interpretation

mnist <- dslabs::read_mnist()
str(mnist)

Lets draw a sample image.

## the labels for this image is: 
mnist$test$labels[i]
[1] 7
mnist_mat <- mnist$train$images %>% 
  unlist() 

mnist_mat <- mnist_mat / 255

pca_mnist <- gmodels::fast.prcomp(mnist_mat)

x_ <- 1
y_ <- 2

yolo <- 
  pca_mnist$x[, 1:4] %>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  mutate(label = mnist$train$labels) %>%
  sample_frac(0.05) 

yolo %>%
  ggplot(aes_string(paste0("PC", x_), paste0("PC", y_), color = "label")) +
  geom_point(data = yolo %>% select(-label), color = "grey60", shape = ".") +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) + 
  scale_color_viridis_c(breaks = 0:10) +
  guides(color = guide_colorbar()) +
  labs(color = "Digit") +
  facet_wrap(~label)

x_ <- 3
y_ <- 4

yolo %>%
  ggplot(aes_string(paste0("PC", x_), paste0("PC", y_), color = "label")) +
  geom_point(data = yolo %>% select(-label), color = "grey60", shape = ".") +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) + 
  scale_color_viridis_c(breaks = 0:10) +
  guides(color = guide_colorbar()) +
  labs(color = "Digit") +
  facet_wrap(~label)
